</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="C815883FFF91FFC8D2E8FBC8FE24FBE7" box="[424,474,1122,1143]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D177FBC8FD01FBE7" authority="Knight" authorityName="Knight" box="[567,767,1121,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D177FBC8FD51FBE7" box="[567,687,1121,1143]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Litura unda</emphasis>
Knight
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF91FFC8D3D7FB0EFAA0FAFF" blockId="16.[151,1436,1188,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<bibRefCitation id="733F4B6CFF91FFC8D3D7FB0EFEB8FB2D" author="Knight" box="[151,326,1188,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refString="Knight, W. J. (1970 b) Two new genera of leafhoppers related to Hishimonus Ishihara (Hom., Cicadellidae). Suomen Hyonteistieteellinen Aikakauskirja, 36, 174 - 182." type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="b">
Knight (
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D3B5FB0EFED1FB2D" box="[245,303,1188,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="1970.0">1970</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
has adequately characterised the genus. It can be readily recognized externally as follows: small black spot one on either side of median line on the hind margin of crown and another spot posterior to it on pronotum; forewings as in 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D28DFB46FDADFA95" box="[461,595,1260,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D28DFB46FDADFA95" box="[461,595,1260,1285]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Hishimonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but dark brown border to median spot much wider laterally and forming conspicuous oval patch in inner discal cell; aedeagus with two shafts each elongate, simple, directed posteriorly at base and curving dorsally with gonopore apical or subapical on posterior surface, with or without lamellate expansion near midlength; preatrium extending ventrally with pair of elongate posteriorly directed processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF91FFC8D387FAD6FD3EFA4C" blockId="16.[151,1436,1188,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Profemur with AD row of setae in basal 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D1CCFAD6FD43FA05" box="[652,701,1404,1429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="0.75">0.75</number>
length, short; AM 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D0D0FAD6FC67FA04" box="[912,921,1404,1428]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
large, AV setae stout, of uniform size in basal half length; intercalary row in abbreviated semicircle consisting of slender long setae. Fore tibia with 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D630FA0AFA84FA28" box="[1392,1402,1440,1464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D6CCFA0AFA62FA28" box="[1420,1436,1440,1464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
(AD+PD) setae. 
<collectingCountry id="6FB9760DFF91FFC8D212FA6EFE74FA4D" box="[338,394,1476,1501]" name="India" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Hind</collectingCountry>
femoral chaetotaxy 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D130FA6EFD7EFA4C" box="[624,640,1476,1500]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D1D1FA6EFD5FFA4C" box="[657,673,1476,1500]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D1F2FA6EFD42FA4C" box="[690,700,1476,1500]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF91FFC8D387FA4DFD0AF9B5" blockId="16.[151,1436,1188,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Female first and second pair of valvulae as in 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D1A2FA4DFC96F990" box="[738,872,1511,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D1A2FA4DFC96F990" box="[738,872,1511,1536]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Hishimonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Seventh sternite with posterior margin medially produced into lobe with deep V-shaped median notch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5FB46516FF91FFC8D387F985FD15F948" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1711369DFF91FFC8D387F985FD15F948" blockId="16.[151,1436,1188,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D387F985FECAF9D8" bold="true" box="[199,308,1583,1608]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Remarks</emphasis>
. The genus was so far reported only from 
<collectingCountry id="6FB9760DFF91FFC8D055F985FC79F9D8" box="[789,903,1583,1608]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. Though 
<bibRefCitation id="733F4B6CFF91FFC8D0B1F985FAC9F9D8" author="Malhotra" box="[1009,1335,1583,1608]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refString="Malhotra, Y. R. &amp; Sharma, B. (1977) A new species of Litura from Jammu, India (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Oriental Insects, 11, 27 - 29. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1977.10432079" type="journal article" year="1977">
Malhotra and Sharma (
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D7B4F99AFAD0F9D8" box="[1268,1326,1584,1608]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="1977.0">1977</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D3D7F9FFFDA2F9FD" authority="Malhotra &amp; Sharma" authorityName="Malhotra &amp; Sharma" box="[151,604,1620,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bharatiensis">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D3D7F9FFFE8EF9FD" box="[151,368,1620,1645]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Litura bharatiensis</emphasis>
Malhotra &amp; Sharma
</taxonomicName>
, this species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D08EF9FFFBEAF9FC" box="[974,1044,1621,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D08EF9FFFBEAF9FC" box="[974,1044,1621,1644]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Litura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but probably to the African genus 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D3D7F9DDFDF9F91F" authority="Linnavuori. However" authorityName="Linnavuori. However" box="[151,519,1655,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Libengaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D3D7F9DDFEF7F900" box="[151,265,1655,1680]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Libengaia</emphasis>
Linnavuori. However
</taxonomicName>
, more detailed studies are needed on this species. A careful examination of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D221F936FD67F925" authority="Li" authorityName="Li" box="[353,665,1692,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripunctatus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D221F936FD89F924" box="[353,631,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Hishimonus tripunctatus</emphasis>
Li
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="733F4B6CFF91FFC8D18BF936FC97F924" author="Li" box="[715,873,1692,1717]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refString="Li, Z., Dai, R. &amp; Xing J. (2011) Deltocephalinae from China (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Popular Science Press, Beijing, China, 336 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Li 
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D1ACF937FCDEF925" box="[748,800,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D070F936FC97F924" box="[816,873,1692,1716]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) revealed that it belongs to this genus and hence 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D3D7F96BFE60F948" authority="Li" authorityName="Li" box="[151,414,1727,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripunctatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D3D7F96BFE95F948" box="[151,363,1729,1752]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Litura tripunctatus</emphasis>
(Li)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3EE957F4FF91FFC8D2E4F915FDDBF948" box="[420,549,1727,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D2E4F915FDDBF948" bold="true" box="[420,549,1727,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is proposed here.
</paragraph>
